title: For Sale:  1955 Chinese Type 53 Mosin Carbine
postcontent: What I have for sale is my beautiful Type 53 Mosin Nagant. It is a Sino-Soviet dated 1955 made at the Jianshe Arsenal in China, /26\. Everything matches except the markings on the magazine floorplate. This isn't from one of the recent batches being sold, it bears no import marks and came in this country before 1989 (That I am absolutely sure of). Bore and chamber are in impeccable condition, Deep strong shiny rifling with 0 pitting of any kind. Action is incredibly slick and easy to operate. It also accepts and feeds from stripper clips properly (No need to use the top round as leverage, you just insert and push down on the rounds). Stock is very nice with absolutely no cracks or repairs. This is not an Arsenal refinished rifle. Super accurate, overall I'd rate it at about 90% Condition wise which is being generous.
